ON the eve of Kenya’s court ruling on the country’s recent
elections, the AU has urged all parties to accept whatever ruling is handed
down.Kenya went to the polls on 8 August. The electoral
commission found that Uhuru Kenyatta and his party won the polls by 54% of the votes,
while Raila Odinga’s party got 45% of the votes.The National Super Alliance (Nasa), headed by veteran
politician Odinga (72), claims to have evidence of “massive irregularities” in
