electoral commission was mysteriously found dead just days before the election,
allegedly with torture marks on his body. This was seen as particularly
threatening to fair elections because of the new electronic system Kenya used
to register votes. There were fears that the electronic system may have been
hacked.The voting went off with little violence, but panic gripped the
cities of Kenya. Nobody has forgotten the tragic and bloody aftermath of the
contested 2007 elections, in which about 1 200 people were killed and 600 000
displaced.According to the Daily
Nation, the AU asked all political parties and their supporters “to avoid
making irresponsible statements or engaging in actions meant to incite violence
and destroying the prevailing peace in Kenya”.